unlock.description:

quality.description:

language.title: __**Help**__: **(language)**
language.description:
__Usage__: **<prefix>language [langcode]**
Changes the language of the server.

__Sample__: **<prefix>language "de"**

prefix.title: __**Help**__: **(prefix)**
prefix.description:
__Usage__: **<prefix>prefix [new_prefix]**
Changes the prefix.

If you have spaces in your prefix use quotes like this:
**<prefix>prefix "new prefix"**

__Sample__: **<prefix>prefix "t! "**

talkcategory.title: __**Help**__: **(talkCategory)**
talkcategory.description:
__Usage__: **<prefix>talkCategory [new_talk_category_name]**
Changes the Category the Bot is managing.

If you have spaces in your category name use quotes like this:
**<prefix>talkcategory "talk category"**

__Sample__: **<prefix>talkCategory "Inf Talks"**

talknamerules.title: __Help__: **(talkNameRules)**
talknamerules.description:
__**Usage**__: **<prefix>talkNameRules [new_talk_name_rules]**
Changes the talk-name-rules for all channels in <category>.

If you have spaces in your talk nameing rule use quotes like this:
**<prefix>talkNameRules "new talk name rules"**

__Sample__: **<prefix>talkNameRules "[lock_sym] Talk [num] - [quality]"**
